physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Ultrasound exam showed reduced amniotic fluid (AFI: 73 mm) and estimated fetal weight of 1559 g (1st percentile). Fetal Doppler indicated umbilical artery PI of 1.23 (96th percentile) and middle cerebral artery PI of 1.62 (16th percentile).
physical_examinations.changes_over_time: After seven days (at 34 weeks and 6 days gestation), ultrasound confirmed reduced amniotic fluid (AFI: 70 mm) and showed umbilical artery PI of 1.27 (98th percentile) and middle cerebral artery PI of 1.21 (1st percentile).

physical_examinations.relevant_findings: Cardiotocographic examinations showed normal baseline heart rate, presence of accelerations, absence of decelerations, and no uterine contractions, with short-term variability always >4.5 ms.
